00:24:39.790 --> 00:24:43.160
So,
the first question I'd like to address,

00:24:43.210 --> 00:24:48.530
of course, is why will mobile,
when combined with media, be successful?

00:24:48.610 --> 00:24:53.700
So, what's so interesting about the
mobile network that will allow for

00:24:53.870 --> 00:24:56.580
better services of media content?

00:24:56.710 --> 00:25:01.770
Well, as a start-off,
what I've put on as a slide is the

00:25:02.150 --> 00:25:08.600
huge number of mobile subscribers
that we address today with 2G,

00:25:08.600 --> 00:25:10.600
2.5G, and 3G networks.

00:25:10.600 --> 00:25:15.590
As you can see, in 2004,
we have roughly 1.3 billion

00:25:15.590 --> 00:25:19.600
subscribers that are covered
with mobile phone technology.

00:25:19.630 --> 00:25:26.590
Now, this 1.3 billion subscribers are
potential subscribers for media content,

00:25:26.710 --> 00:25:31.600
and we see another billion of growth
within the next four to five years.

00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:36.740
So, that's the amount of potential
revenue or potential customers that

00:25:36.740 --> 00:25:39.600
the mobile media industry will have.

00:25:39.600 --> 00:25:46.600
We see a lot of growth in
areas such as Asia Pacific,

00:25:46.600 --> 00:25:51.600
specifically talking about, let's say,
China and India.

00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:56.600
We see in China alone a growth of
